  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Diagnosis of Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease (COPD) (moderate-to-severe as
             classified by the Global Initiative for Chronic Obstructive Lung Disease (GOLD)
             Guidelines, 2007) and:

          -  Post-bronchodilator forced expiratory volume in 1 second (FEV1) &lt;80% and ≥30% of the
             predicted normal value

          -  Post-bronchodilator FEV1/FVC (Forced Vital Capacity) &lt;70%

          -  Current COPD bronchodilator treatment that includes a LABA bronchodilator or a fixed
             dose combination of LABA and Inhaled Corticosteroid (ICS)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with a history of asthma

          -  Patients who are currently being treated for COPD with tiotropium (Spiriva®)

          -  Patients with diabetes Type I or uncontrolled diabetes Type II

          -  Patients with a history of certain cardiovascular comorbid conditions

        Other protocol-defined inclusion/exclusion criteria may apply
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
